{"parse":{"title":"pear tree","pageid":852314,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|peartree|Pear Tree}}\n==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|peartree}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|peretre}}, {{m|enm|pertre}}, {{m|enm|pere tre}}; equivalent to {{af|en|pear|tree}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˌpɛə ˈtɹiː/|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-pear tree.wav|a=Southern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˌpɛɚ ˈtɹi/|a=GA}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Flame, not lame-pear tree.wav|a=US}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A tree of the genus {{taxfmt|Pyrus|genus}}, which bears the [[pear]]s as fruits.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1780|author=unknown author|title=[[w:Twelve Days of Christmas_(song)|Twelve Days of Christmas]]\n|passage=On the first day of Christmas, my true love sent to me<br>A partridge in a '''pear tree'''}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{l|en|tree}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|and a partridge in a pear tree}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|tree of the genus ''Pyrus''}}\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|аҳаҵла}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|[[شَجَرَةُ]] [[كمثرى|اَلكُمَّثْرَى]]|f}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|տանձենի}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|per}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|peral|m|f}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|udareondo}}, {{t+|eu|madariondo}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|гру́ша|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|кру́ша|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|perer|m}}, {{t|ca|perera|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|梨樹|tr=líshù}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|hrušeň|f}}, {{t+|cs|hruška|f}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|perenboom}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|päärynäpuu}}, {{t+|fi|päärynä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|poirier|m}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|piruçâr|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|pereira|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Birnbaum|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|körtefa}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|pero|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t|ja|梨の木|tr=なしのき, nashi no ki}}\n* Macedonian: {{t+|mk|кру́ша|f}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|peretre}}, {{t|enm|pirie}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|pyrige}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Bäarenboom|m}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|grusza|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|pereira|f}}\n* Punjabi: {{t+|pa|ਨਾਸ਼ਪਾਤੀ|f}}, {{t|pa|ਨਾਖ|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|păr}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|гру́ша|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hruška|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|hruška|n}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|kšuška|f}}, {{t|dsb|kšušcyna|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|peral|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|päronträd|n}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|armut ağacı}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|гру́ша|f}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|hàkhàkopëlìshakw}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===References===\n* {{pedia}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aeeeprrt|repartee|rerepeat|repartée|rape tree|repeater}}\n\n{{cln|en|pleonastic compound nouns}}\n{{C|en|Pome fruits}}"}}